chunk_content: (MER v2.6.1 to v2.7): • Added new HTS modality to separate PMTCT Post ANC1 Pregnant/L&D/Breastfeeding modality into two modalities to better account for maternal retesting practices: o Post ANC1 Pregnant/L&D o Post ANC1 Breastfeeding Reporting level: Facility & Community Reporting Quarterly frequency: How to use: As countries progress toward global targets, surveillance of newly diagnosed persons will ensure that interventions reach populations at highest risk of acquiring or transmitting HIV infection. One approach is to identify recent HIV infections, defined as those acquired within approximately the last one year. Use of rapid tests for recent HIV-1 infection (RTRI), in conjunction with viral load testing as indicated in the recent infection testing algorithm (RITA), will facilitate the establishment of a surveillance system to detect, monitor, and characterize recent infections among newly diagnosed HIV cases.
